.jpeg" height="915" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.316115519&amp;id=fig12c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.316115519/asset/images/115519fig13a.jpeg" height="916" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.316115519&amp;id=fig13a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.316115519/asset/images/115519fig13b.jpeg" height="917" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.316115519&amp;id=fig13b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.316115519/asset/images/115519fig14.jpeg" height="914" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig14" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14</span> Primary systemic amyloidosis in a 39-year-old man with gross hematuria and bladder involvement. Coronal unenhanced reformatted CT image shows a high-attenuation blood clot (*) within a diffusely thick-walled bladder (arrows). Cystoscopy showed hemorrhagic cystitis and the blood clot. At cystoscopic biopsy of the urinary bladder, submucosal hemorrhage with associated intramural vascular and submucosal amyloid deposition was present. The patient died 16 months after the initial diagnosis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.316115519&amp;id=fig14">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Gertz MA, Lacy MQ, Dispenzieri A, Hayman SR. Amyloidosis: diagnosis and management. <em>Clin Lymphoma Myeloma</em> 2005;6(3):208–219.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.3816/CLM.2005.n.048">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16354326/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Amyloidosis%3A+diagnosis+and+management&amp;author=MA+Gertz&amp;author=MQ+Lacy&amp;author=A+Dispenzieri&amp;author=SR+Hayman&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;journal=Clin+Lymphoma+Myeloma&amp;pages=208-219&amp;doi=10.3816%2FCLM.2005.n.048&amp;pmid=16354326">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">2.</div><div id="r2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Georgiades CS, Neyman EG, Barish MA, Fishman EK. Amyloidosis: review and CT manifestations. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2004;24(2):405–416.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.242035114">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15026589/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Amyloidosis%3A+review+and+CT+manifestations&amp;author=CS+Georgiades&amp;author=EG+Neyman&amp;author=MA+Barish&am